Q: Spring Boot: Default value in application.properties not used when environment variable is missing in Docker A: <p>You should try injecting both env value the default value elsewhere, than in application.properties.</p>
<p>Do this:</p>
<p><strong>application.properties</strong></p>
<pre class="lang-ini prettyprint-override"><code>host.default=http://host.com
organization.id.default=123
contenttype.id.default=110
</code></pre>
<p>Then inject all directly into ConfigProperties:</p>
<pre class="lang-java prettyprint-override"><code>@Configuration
@Getter
@Setter
public class ConfigProperties {

    @Value(&quot;${HOST:${host.default}}&quot;)
    private String host;

    @Value(&quot;${ORGANIZATION_ID:${organization.id.default}}&quot;)
    private String organizationId;

    @Value(&quot;${CONTENTTYPE_ID:${contenttype.id.default}}&quot;)
    private String contentTypeId;
}
</code></pre>
